---
import DocLayout from "../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout title="Manual Installation">
  <h1>Manual Installation (Vendorizing)</h1>
  
  <p>
    <strong>Tempo</strong> was specifically designed to be <strong>copied and pasted</strong> (vendorized) into your project. This avoids bloating your <code>package.json</code> with external dependencies for a relatively small utility.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Vendorize</h2>
  <p>Follow these steps to include Tempo in your project:</p>

  <ol class="steps steps-vertical">
    <li class="step">
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3 class="font-bold">Locate the Source</h3>
        <p>In the Tempo repository, find the <code>src/</code> directory.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="step">
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3 class="font-bold">Copy to Your Project</h3>
        <p>Copy the contents of <code>src/</code> into a directory in your project (e.g., <code>src/utils/tempo/</code>).</p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="step">
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3 class="font-bold">Import and Use</h3>
        <p>Import the <code>tempo</code> function from the entry point (usually <code>index.ts</code>).</p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>File Structure</h2>
  <p>The library is organized into cohesive modules:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>index.ts</code>: Main entry point and range logic.</li>
    <li><code>parser.ts</code>: Natural language parsing logic.</li>
    <li><code>utils.ts</code>: Pure utility functions (normalization, formatting).</li>
    <li><code>types.ts</code>: TypeScript definitions.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="alert alert-warning shadow-sm mt-8">
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-current shrink-0 h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" /></svg>
    <div>
      <h3 class="font-bold">Maintainer Note</h3>
      <p>When vendorizing, remember to also copy the tests (<code>src/index.test.ts</code>) if you plan to modify the code locally. This ensures your changes don't introduce regressions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocLayout>